18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
20 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 70 of Title 62, unless there is
21 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
22 A. The State Treasurer or a third-party vendor contracted by
23 the Treasurer's office, shall be authorized to issue a transaction
24 card to United States citizens with the ability to make purchases
Req. No. 12932 Page 1

1 that are debited from the balance of deposits with a bullion
2 depository created by the Treasurer’s office or contracted with
3 other public or private entities operating a bullion depository.
4 B. Upon the creation of a depository or a contractual agreement
5 with an entity pursuant to subsection A of this section, the
6 Treasurer’s office shall:
7 1. Provide procedures for the sharing of account information
8 between the depository and the Treasurer upon consent of the account
9 holder; and
10 2. Develop a fee structure for both the depository and the
11 Treasurer, to be paid by the account holder, to utilize the service
12 provided by a bullion depository.
13 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 70.1 of Title 62, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. Deposits of gold and silver in the bullion depository and
17 transactions made using the transaction card issued by the State
18 Treasurer shall be considered legal tender, pursuant to the
19 authority vested upon this state in Section 10 of Article I of the
20 United States Constitution. Deposits of gold and silver in the
21 bullion depository shall not be considered a commodity. The
22 transfer, buying, or selling of gold and silver held in the
23 depository for transactions shall not be considered an exchange of a
24 commodity, and shall be considered an exchange of currency.
